import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay Time')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    average_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    plt.bar(['Average Distance'], [average_distance])
    plt.axhline(average_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {average_distance:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average distance traveled by flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group by origin and destination and count the number of flights
    flights_count = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).size().reset_index(name='count')

    # Sort by count in descending order
    flights_count = flights_count.sort_values('count', ascending=False)

    # Create a bar chart
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    flights_count.plot(kind='bar', x=['origin', 'destination'], y='count', ax=ax, legend=False)

    # Set title and labels
    plt.title('Which origin and destination airports have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Origin and Destination Airports')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')

    # Rotate x-axis labels for better readability
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.date
    flight_dates_count = data['date'].value_counts().sort_index()
    
    plt.plot(flight_dates_count.index, flight_dates_count.values)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.title('Distribution of Flight Dates', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
